Module: keepnick
Author: Brian Weiss <brian@epicsol.org>

Description:
   Keepnick/Getnick services. Getnick is used to gain a nick as soon as it
   becomes available. Keepnick monitors your own nick and runs getnick when
   needed.

Config Variables:
   KEEPNICK                - Boolean. Turns keepnick on/off.
   KEEPNICK_NICK           - If keepnick is on, run getnick if this is not
                             our current nick.

Commands:
   getnick <nick|->
     - Uses the internal notify list to try to regain <nick>. 
     - Passing '-' for the nick argument will disable getnick.

